[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Considering test initialization**\n\nI’m wondering if initializing globally once in a test might affect others. Since tests run in the same JVM, it could be unpredictable. Existing tests stick to defaults, but if I set custom access, could it mess with future tests? I think limiting access to one test class might be wiser. The global once seems irreversible, which could be problematic. Also, I’m exploring alternatives for constructor visibility—there seem to be some intricacies with protected access I need to unravel!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0c7ba5d74865d9270169f7dfb71220819f81bf93e84177f358\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp99-6WEZVhY4nCMueWc5tiYlW3zHOmPC-UThiLTFpTxgeDJa28vHQoIxmFHljRSoYVsW7zktrqrm5wA6Pk7iPURbiVL9jWZtuCFY2-Dpr2etM45Zp6TheaYUF6MWh-TU-SpJhP_cRFLbZ4zEgTmCmgFxS_-M4SsCqHr-LxDavE0cNBWmQgJnaXMycE7N-qRd8_ZsVBeudsF8ov_-i5tz42DwMiEVzJKeeHLjSLJzRqy8FRT47GnxSkmpZpw4c0DwqsF4RkevpzdbfEz5_-6gANJhE3dGBMQh9gfAnVOpvSfVuPswbyercscv-Ie3L5B22GxszyHbF8eHfTDb3oJYrH3Wiu0v8CPpSN8fsBTxIU9MGqrisG1fDWI06Vcan3LymPAyjZti2a9oc8f10lHlVhxHST7npw6FCluo7OthRrm0JomfNRiZjBkXu2exuHo94ZA1zy40zxHFguAajDJzJtMCU9J-KfhqQ9uO2lX4QStb4X61B-G5U4YvQaCHS8SnPsmeWpOLp0cmnt6EucmGnAdEuP_Le076l8PL8_NVGODp4YROmD3L6Z1Be92ID-doCKlyY2HLB84cZzaEY0icf3VK0E1f_qd_lTkEzSjeH3DVbOhBmzaxJahi4YeUMjaoZ0zrCvdhE3DDlqFqroFyhEifCiHgCKCA-6NP7rRIX02QYyW-1z9rbSnUOkO4PLwxB3iH3baTSu3aQzzwQpdC-8XIlfJd50OHNWKdvURle4XuY5Bi3KHmUtybAMh7XYcj0h6WjojzLAa99cMo4Aek1jwcosMKS_1KU5fRuQLsX1TkuNEOG_gYJ9YYoC7RR9A6IjPqWSIwmn8g96X2k200HJDJCLzDfWwVj54xHwdzLfoQ4HXeHJEGCctrVCxvSR6KDBzEsfl9vV1mZ9gB3wfsJm63tYgjZIIZIDotD8M25tJXiaeGqlTTsSbHSshci3B7MRv04EoF8mhgYz6iwAcNQZjZ_YioNJYgQwxghhVHZuEXGopXpXfyQF4hUhVrxReE4NiH8DkkY4nRpcxw7snIGmNFVVm7F3PcYzvhHoy41KFN3vriaHod9e7QLZ4RT0bqbCwLgbItrN8p69ikDh0ibwm6_0YIlH_lb-7NY5VfMbck9Hskj7vRpna4sP2PCApnhFZAXlqqfiJBRskffsXGhodi8RMa9CzatguxtAqAbwqbQ5jRspY5CZb2hIg4XIrtfVpIZj9